assessment_details.task_description:
The purpose of these journal entries is to stimulate a professional discussion between you and the Course Coordinator to review your perceptions of your performance and to coach and support you. The journal entries will be read only by the Course Coordinator. As part of your work placement you need to complete a minimum of four online journal entries of @250 – 300 words about your experience in your workplace. These reflective entries will be based on consideration of how you are using your knowledge and attributes and how you are facing challenging work tasks.

As a guideline, at least one entry per week or per 30-40 hours is suggested. However, some students may enjoy reflecting more often.

As the placement arrangements vary between students, the Course Coordinator will suggest the timing of journal entries with each student during the individual coaching sessions.

There are suggestions for the design and content for each journal entry. However, the final reflective journal entry must be written as a response to the workplace supervisor's feedback which evaluates your performance against the objectives you were given at the start and will consider:

the student's attendance and participation in the placement organisation;

how well the objectives set in the Learning Agreement were met;

the advice of the Workplace Supervisor as set out in the Evaluation Form;

any matters that may impact the student's performance and;

any other relevant factors

A copy of the feedback form can be found in the assessment folder and is to be given to your supervisor at the start of your placement. The workplace supervisor will return the completed form to you during your last week for you to use in your reflective journal.

The forms are given in the assessment folder for the Reflective Journal in Blackboard. Feedback will be given soon after they are posted online to guide and assist you as you develop your reflective entries. The reflective journal will be given a final mark when the last journal entry is submitted.
